    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 mins)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-spiced-tofu-sofritas-bowl/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 30 secs or until the spices are fragrant</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-spiced-tofu-sofritas-bowl/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and stir everything together</p><p>Drain the <strong>tofu</strong>, then crumble it into the pan in rough bite-sized pieces and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-spiced-tofu-sofritas-bowl/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[180ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan, mix everything together and cook for 2-3 min or until the tofu begins to soak up the sauce</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-spiced-tofu-sofritas-bowl/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse the <strong>kidney beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-spiced-tofu-sofritas-bowl/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze the pouch<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span> of <strong>steamed brown basmati rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Add the <strong>steamed basmati rice</strong> and<strong> kidney beans</strong> to the pan with a splash of water, stir everything together and cook for 3-4 min or until the rice is warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>spiced tofu sofritas</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-spiced-tofu-sofritas-bowl/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, finely dice the<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-spiced-tofu-sofritas-bowl/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spiced tofu sofritas </strong>in bowls and top with the <strong>diced tomato</strong> and <strong>fried onions</strong></p><p>Roughly tear over the <strong>coriander </strong>and season with a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
